ing dissection flaps (arrows in f) (Svensson classification type 3). (g) Left anterior oblique three-dimensional volume-rendered CT image shows the focal outpouching (arrow) of the ascending aortic wall between the small intimal tears of the dissection."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2021200055/asset/images/large/rg.2021200055.fig26d.jpeg" height="820" width="721" aria-labelledby="fig26d" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 26d</span>. Limited intimal tear of the ascending aorta in a 72-year-old man who fell and hurt his chest on a table, with subsequent unrelenting chest pain. <b>(a–f)</b> Axial ECG-gated CT images show a dilated ascending thoracic aorta, with a small subtle intimal flap along the medial aspect of the mid to distal ascending thoracic aorta (arrow in <b>a–e</b>), with focal bulging of the ascending thoracic aorta, which is better appreciated on the coronal oblique reformation <b>(f)</b>, in between the small spiraling dissection flaps (arrows in <b>f</b>) (Svensson classification type 3). <b>(g)</b> Left anterior oblique three-dimensional volume-rendered CT image shows the focal outpouching (arrow) of the ascending aortic wall between the small intimal tears of the dissection.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2021200055&amp;id=fig26d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig26e" class="graphic" aria-label="Limited intimal tear of the ascending aorta in a 72-year-old man who fell and hurt his chest on a table, with subsequent unrelenting chest pain. (a–f) Axial ECG-gated CT images show a dilated ascending thoracic aorta, with a small subtle intimal flap along the medial aspect of the mid to distal ascending thoracic aorta (arrow in a–e), with focal bulging of the ascending thoracic aorta, which is better appreciated on the coronal oblique reformation (f), in between the 